<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{y}={14}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{3}{y}=-{45}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{y}={14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={14}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{14}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{\left(\frac{{{14}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+{3}{y}=-{45}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{5}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left({14}\right)}-\frac{{5}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left({2}\right)}{y}+{3}{y}=-{45}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{17.5}-{\left({2.5}\right)}{y}+{3}{y}=-{45}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2.5}{y}+{\left({3}\right)}{y}=-{45}--{17.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2.5}{y}+{\left({3}\right)}{y}=-{27.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({2.5}+{\left({3}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{27.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5.5}{y}=-{27.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{27.5}}{{5.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{\left(-{5}\right)}={14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left(-{10}\right)}={14}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={14}-{\left(-{10}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{24}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

